g.text: EntitySpecification is a class that offers
characteristics to describe a type of entity.
Entities are generic constructs that may be
used to describe bespoke business entities
that are not effectively covered by the
existing SID model. Functionally, the entity
specification acts as a template by which
entities may be instantiated and described.

entities would therefore share the same set
